### Breaking changes affecting your project

1. **`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body.

### Other breaking changes to be aware of

Even though these don't appear in your current code, watch for them elsewhere:

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` constructor | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |
| `TestCase.Id` changed | Test history re-baselines in Azure DevOps |
| `TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors` now `true` | Fix warnings or set to `false` in `.runsettings` |

### Your fixed code would look like:

